    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p>A broom of animated attack is easily mistaken for a broom of flying. It attacks any creature that grabs it or tries to ride it.</p><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><span class=\"rd__h rd__h--3\" data-title-index=\"362\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Flying Broom.</span></span> <p>Some brooms of animated attack allow their creators to ride them, in which case they behave like typical brooms of flying. A broom of animated attack, however, can carry only half the weight that a broom of flying can (see chapter 7, \"Treasure,\" of the Dungeon Master's Guide).</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div></div></div>",
